 need to check if any untracked metadata exists. It looks like adding JUnit BOM under Spring is the right approach. There are several potential issues regarding field injection and test configurations that I need to further investigate, especially around the restrictions of public access and how parameters are handled.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JUnit class template considerations**\\n\\nWhile executing the class template, I see that `Launcher.discover` can invoke a recursive discovery process, which is promising. However, there's a potential issue if it discovers `TestClassScannerTest`. If it does, `expandJupiterClassTemplateIfNecessary` might add nested classes, leading to complications with non-static `@Nested` classes. I also need to be cautious about native image generation and existing metadata, particularly under `src/test/resources`, and ensure we're maintaining compatibility with JUnit BOM 6.0.0 without hardcoding artifact versions unnecessarily.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing test class inclusion**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to include an untracked test file in the diff stat. Git diff doesn't include untracked files with `--stat`, which is fine. I’m also thinking about checking existing resource reachability, but maybe that’s unnecessary. Additionally, I should decide whether to include the `@ParameterizedClass` at the top level in `TestClassScannerTest`, since it matches the dynamic class name. I realize that all top-level test classes need to be public, so that’s something to keep in mind!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `org.springframework.test.context.aot.TestClassScanner`.\n\nChanges made:\n- Added `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_test/TestClassScannerTest.java`\n  - Exercises Spring’s public `TestAotProcessor` path.\n  - Scans the compiled test classpath.\n  - Uses a JUnit class template with a `@Nested` test class so `TestClassScanner.collectNestedTestClasses()` reaches `Class#getDeclaredClasses()`.\n- Updated `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle`\n  - Added JUnit 6 BOM and `junit-jupiter-params` for `@ParameterizedClass` support.\n\nI did not modify reachability metadata or native-image resource configuration files, and I did not run compilation or tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_066a4efdf43e1567016a28337d57a08195950815136c47198d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 391, "output": 1215, "cacheRead": 41984, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 43590, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781019490885, "responseId": "resp_066a4efdf43e1567016a28336377ac8195972c3ddfe06ec829"}, "toolResults": []}
